Install Git for your device,then in the command prompt check whether it is installed by using git in cmd.
Step 1 : Create repository (don't forget to click readme and license)
Step 2 : Copy git repository link
Step 3 : Create new folder (d:/NmvmJSD)
Step 4 : Open cmd : d: /nmvm> git clone Paste git link
Step 5 : cd git repository
Step 6 : code .
Step 7 : add files (create files)
Step 8 : git add .
Step 9 : git commit -m "Your Message" (on 1st time : verify email & user)
Step 10 : git push
To delete a file
Delete the file in vscode & then git add . & git commit then git push


